Package com.guidewire.util.webservices.login.fault

Exception Summary
AlreadyExecutedException  
BadIdentifierException Thrown when an internal public ID doesn't map to a real bean (problem could be that type was incorrect).
BatchProcessException SOAP Exception specific to batch process operations
DataConversionException Thrown by many APIs when they encounter a problem translating a SOAP data object into an internal system object.
DuplicateKeyException Throws if a duplicate data exception is detected in the database.
EntityStateException Thrown when an attempt is made to manipulate an object that is in a state that prevents the operation from being performed.
FieldConversionException Thrown when a data type cannot be converted into the native data type.
FieldFormatException Thrown when the input type does not match the format specified in the metadata.
LoginException Class of exceptions thrown when a user tries to log in and an authentication failure occurs.
PermissionException Thrown when the authenticated SOAP user does not have permission to perform the requested operation
RequiredFieldException Thrown when required data is missing from a bean.
ServerStateException ServerStateException is thrown when a request is made at a time the server is in a state that disallows the request.
SOAPException A generic SOAP exception.
SOAPSenderException SOAPSenderException is the base class for all exceptions that resulted from a sender error.
SOAPServerException SOAPServerException is the base class for all exceptions that resulted from a server error.
UnknownTypeKeyException Thrown when a typekey value isn't available on the server.
